               <p>579. 
               
                  <persName id="t18200412-228-defend2122" type="defendantName">
                     JOSEPH 
                     HARDING
                  <interp inst="t18200412-228-defend2122" type="surname" value="HARDING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-defend2122" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-defend2122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-defend2122" type="age" value="20"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18200412-228-off1313" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-off1313" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-off1313" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18200412-228-cd1314" type="crimeDate">4th of February</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-228-off1313 t18200412-228-cd1314"></join>, one watch, value 4 l., and four seals, value 2 l., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18200412-228-victim2124" type="victimName">
                           James 
                           Davey
                        <interp inst="t18200412-228-victim2124" type="surname" value="Davey"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18200412-228-victim2124" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18200412-228-victim2124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-228-off1313 t18200412-228-victim2124"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-228-person2125">
                  JAMES 
                  DAVEY
               <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2125" type="surname" value="DAVEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2125" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Harley-street, and am <rs id="t18200412-228-viclabel1315" type="occupation">coachman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-228-victim2124 t18200412-228-viclabel1315"></join> to Mr. Mitchell. On the 4th of February, about half-past six o'clock, I was coming from <placeName id="t18200412-228-crimeloc1316">Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-228-crimeloc1316" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-228-crimeloc1316" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-228-off1313 t18200412-228-crimeloc1316"></join>; at the corner of Portland-place and Devonshire-street I saw two men coming, one was about five yards behind the other - one caught hold of my arm, and the other pulled my watch out instantly and ran away. I called out Stop thief! the other came, took hold of my arm, and asked what he had done? I told him he had taken my watch, and broke from him. He said</p>
               <p>"Come along, I can run faster than you, and I will catch him." He ran a few yards, and then tripped up my heels - I am sure he is one of the two - the other came up the instant I had lost the watch. I never lost sight of the prisoner till he was stopped at the corner of Weymouth-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-228-person2126">
                  JOHN 
                  MAUD
               <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2126" type="surname" value="MAUD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2126" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a gentleman's servant, and live in Portland-place, between Devonshire-street and Weymouth-street. I found the watch in the area on a Thursday, at the latter end of February, about nine o'clock in the evening - it had been thrown there.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-228-person2127">
                  JOHN 
                  MARTIN
               <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2127" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2127" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-person2127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was officer of the night; the prisoner was brought to the watch-house by Oram, about half-past seven o'clock, Davey came down with him, and charged him with robbing him - he told the same story which he has now, and was quite sure the prisoner was one of them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The man has sworn falsely.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-228-verdict1317" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200412-228-verdict1317" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-228-punish1318" type="punishmentDescription">
